#! <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
#! <TRANSFORMER
# TRANSFORMER_BEGIN METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_ERROR_MANAGER,1,"""FGP Tools""",2e8566af-d0b9-44f6-b7e2-7423c70ccaf9,"Linked by Default",No,NO_PARALLELISM,,No,25241,YES,No,313,No,
# <p><strong>Description</strong> </p>
# <p>This custom transformer checks if the input records have mapping errors.  A record has one or more mapping errors if the attribute mapping_errors{}. is present.  If mapping errors are present the individual errors are individually extracted from the list (mapping_errors{} list is exploded) and sent to the ERROR_OUTPUT port. </p>
# <p>Mapping errors are created by the following custom transformers: METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER, METADATA_FORMAT_MAPPER</p>
# <p><strong>Input Ports</strong> </p>
# <p>Input: The input metadata records to process.</p>
# <p><strong>Output Ports </strong></p>
# <p>ERROR_OUTPUT: The detailed list of errors (one record per error)</p>
# <p>DATA_OUTPUT: The metadata record without any mapping error</p>
# <p><strong>Parameters </strong></p>
# <p>None</p>
# TRANSFORMER_END
#!   A0_PREVIEW_IMAGE="data:image/png;base64,"
